<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Hochman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 EAGLES MERCHANDISE: If you are going to the Eagles shows, you'd better buy the 
T-shirts and caps at the concert, because that may be your only chance. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're going the traditional route of selling the merchandise at the venues," 
says tour organizer Irving Azoff."Some things will be available at retail 
stores, but we're not setting up any special things for it." 
</P>
<P>
 And the Eagles' line of souvenirs is nowhere near as extensive as Streisand's. 
Azoff says that the Eagles turned down numerous proposals for souvenirs, though 
some special items (including "Hell Freezes Over" tour drumsticks) are being 
sold, with their proceeds earmarked for charity. 
</P>
<P>
 "What Barbra is doing is fine for her and her audience," he says. "I don't 
think the Eagles audience would respond to it." Steve Hochman 
