<P>
 NIRVANA NUGGET: The first posthumous release of a Nirvana recording is 
coming.A demo for a song titled "Pay to Play" will be featured on "DGC 
Rarities, Vol. 1," a compilation of rare and unreleased tracks from artists on 
the Geffen-owned DGC label. The album is due July 5, with a special $9.98 list 
price for CD and $7.98 for cassette. 
</P>
<P>
 Nirvana fanatics know that the group never recorded an "official" version of 
"Pay to Play," but changed it into "Stay Away," which is on the "Nevermind" 
album. Unfortunately for Nirvana fans, that's the group's only track on this 
collection. Dennis Hunt 
