FOUR-STAR FILMS; 'ATLANTIC CITY' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Directed by Louis Malle and written by John Guare, the 1980 film is an 
exquisite romantic fable and satire of American pop culture, past and present. 
Burt Lancaster and Susan Sarandon are among those dreamers whose lives converge 
in the throes of Atlantic City's renewal, thanks to legalized gambling. A key 
film of the '80s, it is a fairy tale beautifully acted and as funny as it is 
touching (Lifetime Wednesday 10 a.m.). 
