<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Your May 7 editorial, "Dream Team," was right on point. It's about time 
women are competing with men in professional baseball.Baseball is not a sport 
which is based upon strength alone. Speed, coordination and savvy are just a 
few of the essentials of a good baseball player. And women have just as much of 
these qualities as do their male counterparts. 
</P>
<P>
 I hope we will see women playing major-league ball by the end of the decade. 
After all, if 46-year-old men are pitching successfully in the major leagues, 
women in their 20s certainly can play just as well. 
</P>
<P>
 FRED HUEBSCHER 
</P>
<P>
 Hermosa Beach 
