COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: WATTS; CONFERENCE TO FOCUS ON VIOLENCE ISSUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Watts College of Child Development will sponsor its 19th annual Week of 
the Child conference starting June 6. 
</P>
<P>
 The weeklong conference will examine issues of violence in the black 
community, including a panel discussion on how to bridge the gap between older 
adults and youths. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is to let people know that African American children are an endangered 
species, and we need help getting them to the year 2000," said Paul Wilson, a 
member of the organization. 
</P>
<P>
 The college is a non-accredited community organization that focuses on 
children's issues. The conference will be at the Ramada Hotel in Compton. 
</P>
