BOOTH HAS 5-SHOT LEAD IN ARIZONA JUNIOR GOLF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kellee Booth of Coto de Caza shot a four-under-par 68 Saturday to take a 
five-shot lead after the first round of the Girls' Junior Championships golf 
tournament at the Conquistador Country Club in Tucson, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
 Booth shot a 32 on the back nine to open a lead over Jenny Lee of Fullerton 
and three other golfers. 
</P>
<P>
 Jenny Glasgow of Corona del Mar was one of five golfers at 77. 
