<P>
CHINA EXPELS SOUTH KOREAN TV CREW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Chinese government expelled a visiting four-member South Korean television 
crew Friday because they had changed their travel itinerary without permission, 
the South Korean Embassy said. 
</P>
<P>
 The crew, from a provincial affiliate of MBC television, had arrived in China 
with plans to visit the coastal province of Shandong, but instead went to the 
city of Nanjing, Kim Myung-koo of the embassy's information office said. 
</P>
<P>
 Chinese authorities have closely monitored the activities of foreign 
journalists in the weeks leading to the June 4 anniversary of the army attack 
on pro-democracy protesters in 1989. Last week, police burst into the home of 
one of the former 1989 protest leaders, Wang Dan, as he was being interviewed 
by the U.S. television station NBC and led the NBC crew away for questioning 
and reprimand. 
