<P>
ONE SCHOOL BUS TRAGEDY IS TOO MANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 My letter is in regard to the little boy who was hit by a pickup truck when 
crossing the street after getting off the bus. I am a bus driver and I feel 
that a lot of people do not use safety precautions when they see a school 
bus.Any time you pass a school bus, please use caution and please try to slow 
down and also stop when you see the red lights flash. I can't count how many 
times people have run my red lights. 
</P>
<P>
 I am a mother and I really feel sorry for this parent who lost her child, but 
I am also a bus driver who cares about my children who ride on my bus. So, 
please, at all times use extreme caution when passing a school bus. 
</P>
<P>
 CHRISTINE COMLEY 
</P>
