<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL VOLLEYBALL / SOUTHERN SECTION CHAMPIONSHIPS; HUNTINGTON BEACH 
REPEATS AS CHAMPION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntington Beach won its second consecutive Southern Section boys' volleyball 
championship Saturday with a 15-13, 11-15, 15-8, 15-9 victory over Laguna Beach 
in the Division I final at Cerritos College. 
</P>
<P>
 The unseeded Oilers (21-2) avenged a nonleague loss to Laguna Beach on May 
2.Last season, Huntington Beach defeated Capistrano Valley in five games in the 
Division I championship match. 
</P>
<P>
 Dan Styles had 28 kills for Laguna Beach (19-2), but the Oilers' defense made 
the difference. Nick Ziegler had 16 kills, Jeremy Bart 15 and Mike Grave 11 for 
Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 With the match even at one game apiece, the Oilers rallied from a 6-1 in Game 
3 deficit to win 14 of the final 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Division II: Simi Valley Royal defeated Palmdale Highland, 15-10, 15-12, 
11-15, 17-15. Royal rallied from a 13-9 deficit in Game 4 to close out the 
match. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Olsen had 38 kills and setter Josh White had 79 assists to lead 
second-seeded Royal (18-3). Danny Rizzo added 20 kills for the Highlanders. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Millar had 26 kills and six blocks and Mac Wilson had 19 kills and 12 
blocks for top-seeded Highland (18-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Division III: Santa Ana Calvary Chapel defeated Santa Ynez, 15-8, 15-3, 15-8 
behind 20 kills and three blocks from Philip Schildts. Aaron Fountain added 10 
kills for the top-seeded Eagles. Setter Matt Wright had 31 assists for Calvary 
Chapel, which finished the season 18-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Andy Witt had 16 kills and Matt Williams added nine for second-seeded Santa 
Ynez (21-3). 
</P>
</TEXT>
