<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL NOTES; LA QUINTA TO FACE CORONA AT NORCO IN THE SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Quinta will play Corona at Norco High on Tuesday in the Southern Section 
Division III baseball semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
 The Aztecs (26-3), the second-seeded team, likely will start sophomore pitcher 
Joe Garcia.La Quinta has won 19 consecutive games. Corona (22-6-1) is expected 
to start Ed Hurtado. 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel will play Big Bear at Orange Coast College in the Division V 
semifinals. Big Bear (19-7), the defending champion, is the fourth-seeded team. 
Calvary Chapel (21-8), the third-place team from the Olympic League, already 
has upset No. 1-seeded North Hills Los Angeles Baptist. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley (25-3-1) will play La Crescenta Crescenta Valley at Blair 
Field in Long Beach at 7 p.m in the Division I semifinals. The Barons seek to 
be the first No. 1-seeded team to win the large school championship since 
Lakewood did it in 1970. Crescenta Valley (18-5) upset fourth-seeded El Dorado 
in the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jaret Wright of Katella High, expected to be among the first high school 
pitchers chosen in the June free-agent draft, has been selected the Gatorade 
Circle of Champions Pacific regional player of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Wright, whose fastball has been clocked at 94 m.p.h., was 8-2 with a 3.36 
earned-run average. The son of former Angel pitcher Clyde Wright, he led Orange 
County with 112 strikeouts in 83 1/3 innings. 
</P>
<P>
 A co-captain, Wright helped lead Katella to a share of the Empire League 
championship. It was the Knights' first baseball title since 1981. 
</P>
