<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPECIAL REPORT: EXECUTIVE PAY; THE GOLDEN STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The nationwide recession has lingered longest in California, but for top 
executives, it was the place to be in 1993. Median cash compensation rose 10% 
among California's top executives, compared to 8.1% nationwide, according to 
figures from William M. Mercer Inc. in San Francisco. 
</P>
