<HEADLINE>
<P>
36TH BUILDERS, REMODELERS TRADE SHOW SLATED IN S.F. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The 36th annual Pacific Coast Builders Conference, long considered the West's 
premiere building industry trade show, will open June 16 for a three-day run in 
San Francisco's Moscone Center. Reflecting the growing importance of the $105 
billion-a-year U.S. remodeling industry, this PCBC has added "Remodelers Show" 
to its name. 
</P>
<P>
 Some 2,000 home builders and several hundred remodeling contractors, along 
with thousands of members of allied fields, are expected to attend the show, 
which features 55,000 square feet of products and services for the home and 
home-building industry, as well as dozens of educational programs and an 
architecture and design competition. 
</P>
<P>
 A highlight of the show will be New Home 2000, a nine-room model home built on 
the exhibit hall floor and featuring advanced design concepts, construction 
technologies and produce innovations that could reshape home-building and 
consumers' lifestyles in the next century. 
</P>
<P>
 The PCBC exhibit area, which features the latest appliances and products for 
the home from dozens of manufacturers, will be open to consumers on Saturday, 
June 18, for a cost of $15 a person. For more information on the show, call 
(916) 325-9300. 
</P>
