<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLARIFICATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A May 15 article on estate planning reported that the federal estate tax rate 
ranges from 37% to 55% and that there is no California estate tax. Under a form 
of revenue-sharing known as the Credit for State Death Taxes, California shares 
in a portion of the federal estate tax paid by an estate. Although the state 
calls this the California Estate Tax, it is not an additional tax and does not 
increase the total taxes paid by an estate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
