<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPECIAL REPORT / ELECTION PREVIEW; DECISION '94 / A VOTER'S GUIDE TO STATE AND 
LOCAL ELECTIONS; STATEWIDE OFFICES; ABOUT THESE RACES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Voters in the June 7 primary will find an incumbent in only one of the seven 
races for statewide offices below the rank of governor. The rest are open-seat 
contests in a particularly competitive year for statewide office, with 
wide-open campaign free-for-alls. Also listed on these Statewide Offices pages: 
an incumbent facing a serious challenge to his regional seat on the five-member 
Board of Equalization. 
</P>
