<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE ORANGE COUNTY 100 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More Orange County executives than ever were boosted into millionaire status 
last year. Unlike 1992, however, there are no women with million-dollar pay 
packages on the list of the year's 100 most highly compensated executives of 
publicly traded Orange County companies. 
</P>
<P>
 (Legend for title abbreviations: COB=chairman of the board; COE=chief 
executive officer; P=president; COO=chief operating officer; SVP=senior vice 
president; EVP=executive vice president; VP=vice president; CFO=chief financial 
officer; SEC=corporate secretary; CMO=chief medical officer; T=treasurer; 
LC=legal counsel; SO=subsidiary officer): 04,06,14,24,15 Total Rank 
