<P>
 REPUBLICAN PRIMARY 
</P>
<P>
 Christopher Cox 
</P>
<P>
 Age: 41 
</P>
<P>
 Occupation: Incumbent 
</P>
<P>
 Background: Elected to Congress in 1988; attorney; former senior associate 
counsel to President Reagan from 1986 to 1988; Cox and father founded a company 
that translated to English the former Soviet Union newspaper Pravda. 
